source_citation: GFDX
data_choice_notes: Keeping GFDx estimate (16.3%), as it is more recent  (2012-2013, 2017), presumably applies nationally to both urban and rural populations, and cites credible sources including micronutrient surveys and HKI. Discarding estimates from Hess et al. 2010 (92% for WRA, 81% for U5) from FRAT survey, as these were for urban populations only, despite the fact that these numbers also seem credible. We don't have a good way to average the GFDx number and the Hess numbers because we are missing numbers for rural populations, and the values are so different that a simple average seems like it would give the wrong answer.
